            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">HEBREW CONGREGATION</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">OF</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">“THE DISPERSED OF JUDAH.”</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">_______</p>
            <p>SIR—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You are hereby notified that the sale of the seats of the Synagogue
                of this Congregation, will take place<lb/> at the Synagogue on <date>Sunday next,
                    the 29th</date> instant, at 10 o'clock, A. M.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The following are extracts from the minutes of the Board of Officers
                in relation to the sale of the Seats.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The seats are rated as follows:</p>
            <p>ALL THE GENTLEMEN'S First row or front seats each - - 812.00 per annum.</p>
            <p>“““ Second “ “ “ - - 8.00 “ “</p>
            <p>“““ Third “ “ “ - - 5.00 “ “</p>
            <p>“ “LADIES' First row or front seats each - - 10.00 ““</p>
            <p>“““ Second “ “ “ - - 7.50 ““</p>
            <p>“““ Third “ “ “ - - 4.00 ““</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The choice of one, with the privilege of the remaining seats on the
                same bench between arms, shall be sold<lb/> for the term of two years from the
                    <date>29th</date> instant. Rent to be paid monthly: Pre-emption money, to be
                paid at the time<lb/> of sale for the first year, and the same pre-emption at the
                commencement of the second year.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The sale of all seats is thrown open at the above assessed rates,
                and possession given on <date>Friday, the 3d<lb/> April</date> next; all seats
                remaining unsold after the sale, shall be fixed at the average of the entire
                pre-emption, paid at the sale.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Any member who is in arrears six months, shall not be permitted to
                purchase a seat in the Synagogue until<lb/> said arrears are paid up, and it shall
                be discretionary with the Board to deprive any person of his seats, on his
                refusing<lb/> or neglecting to pay for the same punctually every month.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Seats can be purchased after the public sale by applying to the
                President.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The lease of all the seats shall expire at one time, say twenty four
                months from the date of purchase.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Seats to be selected by the purchaser at the time of
                adjudication.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <emph rend="italics">By order of the board.</emph>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)"><persName>ALEX. ABRAMS</persName>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(12)">
                <emph rend="italics">Secretary</emph>
            </p>
            <p><placeName>NEW ORLEANS</placeName>, <date><emph rend="italics">March</emph> 23,
                    1857</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)"><date>5617</date>.</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>Dear <addressee>Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">As I intend to forward<lb/> you exclusively all news<lb/> of the
                Congregation I send you<lb/> the enclosed as a beginning,<lb/> after the
                    <date>1st</date> I will supply<lb/> you with further matter</p>
            <p>Did I mention to you that</p>
